enumDefs.name: AtlasGlossaryTermRelationshipStatus
enumDefs.description: TermRelationshipStatus defines how reliable the relationship is between two glossary terms

elementDefs.description: DRAFT means the relationship is under development.
ACTIVE means the relationship is validated and in use.
DEPRECATED means the the relationship is being phased out.
OBSOLETE means that the relationship should not be used anymore.
OTHER means that there is another status.

enumDefs.name: BusinessCapabilityType
enumDefs.description: Defines the type or category of business capability.

elementDefs.description: The business capability has not been classified.
A functional business capability.
A collection of related business services.
Another governance definition status.

enumDefs.name: ToDoStatus
enumDefs.description: Progress on completing an action (to do).

elementDefs.description: No action has been taken.
Work is underway to complete the action.
Work is blocked waiting for resource of another action to complete.
The action has been completed successfully.
Work has stopped on the action and will not recommence.

enumDefs.name: GovernanceDomain

elementDefs.description: Relevant to all governance domains.
The data (information) governance domain.
The data privacy domain.
The security governance domain.
The IT infrastructure governance domain.
The software development lifecycle governance domain.
The corporate governance domain.
The physical asset management governance domain.
Another governance domain.

enumDefs.name: DataClassAssignmentStatus

elementDefs.description: The data class assignment was discovered by an automated process.
The data class assignment was proposed by a subject matter expert.
The data class assignment was imported from another metadata system.
The data class assignment has been validated and approved by a subject matter expert.
The data class assignment should no longer be used.
The data class assignment must no longer be used.
Another data class assignment status.

enumDefs.name: file_action
enumDefs.description: file_action

enumDefs.name: DiscoveryRequestStatus

enumDefs.name: StarRating
enumDefs.description: Level of support or appreciation for an item.

elementDefs.description: This content is not recommended.
One star rating.
Two star rating.
Three star rating.
Four star rating.
Five star rating.

enumDefs.name: Endianness
enumDefs.description: Defines the sequential order in which bytes are arranged into larger numerical values when stored in memory or when transmitted over digital links.

elementDefs.description: Bits or bytes order from the big end.
Bits or bytes ordered from the little end.

enumDefs.name: AtlasGlossaryTermAssignmentStatus
enumDefs.description: TermAssignmentStatus defines how much the semantic assignment should be trusted.

elementDefs.description: DISCOVERED means that the semantic assignment was added by a discovery engine.
PROPOSED means that the semantic assignment was proposed by person - they may be a subject matter expert, or consumer of the Referenceable asset
IMPORTED means that the semantic assignment has been imported from outside of the open metadata cluster
VALIDATED means that the semantic assignment has been reviewed and is highly trusted.
DEPRECATED means that the semantic assignment is being phased out. There may be another semantic assignment to the Referenceable that will ultimately replace this one.
OBSOLETE means that the semantic assignment is no longer in use,
OTHER means that the semantic assignment value does not match any of the other Term Assignment Status values

enumDefs.name: AnnotationStatus
enumDefs.description: Defines the status of an annotation.

elementDefs.description: The annotation is new.
The annotation has been reviewed by a steward.
The annotation has been approved.
The request has been actioned.
The annotation is invalid or incorrect.
The annotation should be ignored.
Another status.

enumDefs.description: hive_principal_type

The server capability keeps the asset up-to-date.
The server capability consumes the content of the asset.

enumDefs.name: ConfidenceLevel

elementDefs.description: There is no assessment of the confidence level of this data.
The data comes from an ad hoc process.
The data comes from a transactional system so it may have a narrow scope.
The data comes from an authoritative source.
The data is derived from other data through an analytical process.
The data comes from an obsolete source and must no longer be used.
Another confidence level.

enumDefs.name: KeyPattern
enumDefs.description: Defines the type of identifier used for an asset.

elementDefs.description: Unique key allocated and used within the scope of a single system.
Key allocated and used within the scope of a single system that is periodically reused for different records.
Key derived from an attribute of the entity, such as email address, passport number.
Key value copied from another system.
Key formed by combining keys from multiple systems.
Key from another system can bey used if system name provided.
Key value will remain active even if records are merged.
Another key pattern.

enumDefs.name: CommentType
enumDefs.description: Descriptor for a comment that indicated its intent.

elementDefs.description: General comment.
A question.
An answer to a previously asked question.
A suggestion for improvement.
An account of an experience.
None of the above.

enumDefs.name: MediaType

elementDefs.description: The media is an image.
The media is an audio recording.
The media is a text document, probably rich text.
The media is a video recording.
Another type of media, probably not supported.

enumDefs.name: MediaUsage

elementDefs.description: Provides a small image to represent the asset in tree views and graphs.
Provides a small image about the asset that can be used in lists.
Illustrates how the asset works or what it contains. It is complementary to the asset's description.
Provides guidance to a person on how to use the asset.
Another usage.

enumDefs.name: RetentionBasis

elementDefs.description: There is no assessment of the retention requirements for this data.
This data is temporary.
The data is needed for the lifetime of the referenced project.
The data is needed for the lifetime of the referenced team.
The data is needed for the lifetime of the referenced contract.
The retention period for the data is defined by the referenced regulation.
The data is needed for the specified time.
Another basis for determining the retention requirement.

enumDefs.name: DataItemSortOrder

elementDefs.description: Sort the data values so that they increase in value.
Sort the data values so that they decrease in value.

enumDefs.name: OrderBy

elementDefs.description: Order by name property.
Order by owner property.
Order by date added to the metadata collection.

Order by date that the asset was created.
Order by another property.

enumDefs.name: TermRelationshipStatus

The term relationship should no longer be used.
The term relationship must no longer be used.

enumDefs.name: ActivityType

elementDefs.description: Normal processing.

A piece of work for a person, organization or engine.

enumDefs.name: CrowdSourcingRole

elementDefs.description: Actor that creates the initial version.
Actor that provided feedback.
Actor that agrees with the definition.
Actor that declares the definition should be used.

enumDefs.name: ConceptModelAttributeCoverageCategory

elementDefs.description: The attribute's coverage category is unknown - this is the default.
The attribute uniquely identifies the concept bead.
The attribute is a good indicator of the identity of the concept bead but not guaranteed to be unique.
The attribute provides information that is typically required by all of the consumers of the concept bead.
The attribute contains supplementary information that is of interest to specific consumers of the concept bead.

enumDefs.name: ContactMethodType

elementDefs.description: Contact through email.
Contact through telephone number.
Contact through chat account.
Contact through open metadata profile.
Contact through social media or similar account.

enumDefs.name: CriticalityLevel

elementDefs.description: There is no assessment of the criticality of this data.
The data is of minor importance to the organization.
The data is important to the running of the organization.
The data is critical to the operation of the organization.
The data is so important that its loss is catastrophic putting the future of the organization in doubt.

relationshipDefs.name: FolderHierarchy
relationshipDefs.description: A nested relationship between two file folders.

relationshipDefs.name: AtlasGlossarySynonym
relationshipDefs.description: Synonym is a relationship between glossary terms that have the same, or a very similar meaning in the same language. Notice that both ends of this relationship have the same name and refer to the same type; this results in one Synonym attribute being added to GlossaryTerm.

attributeDefs.name: description
attributeDefs.description: The description field can be used to add details about the relationship.

attributeDefs.name: steward
attributeDefs.description: The steward is the person responsible for assessing the relationship and deciding if it should be approved or not.

relationshipDefs.name: AtlasGlossaryReplacementTerm
relationshipDefs.description: ReplacementTerm is a relationship that indicates that the replacementTerm must be used instead of the replacedByTerm. This is stronger version of the PreferredTerm.

attributeDefs.name: description
attributeDefs.description: The description field can be used to add details about the relationship.

attributeDefs.name: steward
attributeDefs.description: The steward is the person responsible for assessing the relationship and deciding if it should be approved or not

attributeDefs.name: annotationType
attributeDefs.description: Name of the type of annotation.

attributeDefs.name: summary

attributeDefs.name: confidenceLevel

attributeDefs.name: explanation

attributeDefs.name: analysisStep
attributeDefs.description: The step in the pipeline that produced the annotation.

attributeDefs.name: jsonProperties
attributeDefs.description: Additional properties used in the specification.

attributeDefs.name: additionalProperties
attributeDefs.description: Additional properties discovered during the analysis.

attributeDefs.name: annotationStatus
attributeDefs.description: Status of the processing as a result of the annotation.

relationshipDefs.name: MoreInformation
relationshipDefs.description: Link to indicate that a referenceable provides additional information about another referenceable.

endDef1.name: providesMoreInformation
endDef1.description: Provides more information about this referenceable.

relationshipDefs.name: ResourceList
relationshipDefs.description: Links supporting resources to an anchor object (typically an Actor Profile, Project, Meeting or Community).

attributeDefs.name: resourceUse
attributeDefs.description: Description of how the resource is used, or why it is useful.

attributeDefs.name: watchResource
attributeDefs.description: Indicator whether the anchor should receive notifications of changes to the resource.

endDef1.name: supportingResources
endDef1.description: Resources identified as of interest to the anchor.

endDef2.name: resourceListAnchors
endDef2.description: Referenceable objects that are using the linked to resource.

relationshipDefs.name: AtlasGlossaryTranslation
relationshipDefs.description: Translation is a relationship that defines that the related terms represent the same meaning, but each are written in a different language. Hence one is a translation of the other. The language of each term is defined in the Glossary object that anchors the term.

attributeDefs.name: description
attributeDefs.description: The description field can be used to add details about the relationship.

attributeDefs.name: steward
attributeDefs.description: The steward is the person responsible for assessing the relationship and deciding if it should be approved or not

relationshipDefs.name: AtlasGlossaryCategoryHierarchyLink
relationshipDefs.description: CategoryHierarchyLink is a relationship used to organize categories into a hierarchy to, for example, create a structure for a taxonomy. A category may have none or one super-categories. This super-category may be in a different glossary.

relationshipDefs.name: AtlasGlossaryTermAnchor
relationshipDefs.description: TermAnchor links each term to exactly one Glossary object. This means that this is its home glossary. If the Glossary object is deleted, then so are all of the terms linked to it.

relationshipDefs.name: AtlasGlossaryCategoryAnchor
relationshipDefs.description: CategoryAnchor links each category to exactly one Glossary object. This means that this is its home glossary. If the Glossary object is deleted then so are all of the categories linked to it.

relationshipDefs.name: AtlasGlossaryValidValue
relationshipDefs.description: ValidValue is a relationship that shows the validValue term represents one of the valid values that could be assigned to a data item that has the meaning described in the validValueFor term.

attributeDefs.name: description
attributeDefs.description: The description field can be used to add details about the relationship.

attributeDefs.name: steward
attributeDefs.description: The steward is the person responsible for assessing the relationship and deciding if it should be approved or not.

relationshipDefs.name: AtlasGlossaryAntonym
relationshipDefs.description: Antonym is a relationship between glossary terms that have the opposite (or near opposite) meaning, in the same language. Notice that both ends of this relationship have the same name and refer to the same type; this results in one Antonym attribute being added to GlossaryTerm.

attributeDefs.name: description
attributeDefs.description: The description field can be used to add details about the relationship.

attributeDefs.name: steward
attributeDefs.description: The steward is the person responsible for assessing the relationship and deciding if it should be approved or not.

relationshipDefs.name: AtlasGlossaryPreferredTerm
relationshipDefs.description: PreferredTerm is a relationship that indicates that the preferredTerm should be used in place of the preferredToTerm. This relationship can be used to encourage adoption of newer vocabularies. This is a weaker version of ReplacementTerm.

attributeDefs.name: description
attributeDefs.description: The description field can be used to add details about the relationship.

attributeDefs.name: steward
attributeDefs.description: The steward is the person responsible for assessing the relationship and deciding if it should be approved or not.

relationshipDefs.name: AtlasGlossarySemanticAssignment
relationshipDefs.description: SemanticAssignment is a relationship used to assign a term to a referenceable object. This means that the term describes the meaning of the referenceable object. The semantic assignment needs to be a controlled relationship when glossary definitions are used to provide classifications for the data assets and hence define how the data is to be governed.

attributeDefs.name: description
attributeDefs.description: The description field can be used to add details about the semantic assignment.

attributeDefs.name: confidence
attributeDefs.description: The confidence attribute in the semantic assignment stores the level of confidence (0-100%) in the correctness of the semantic assignment - it is typically used by discovery engines.

attributeDefs.name: createdBy
attributeDefs.description: The semantic assignment is created by the user (person or engine) identified by the createdBy attribute.

attributeDefs.name: steward
attributeDefs.description: The steward is the person responsible for assessing the semantic assignment and deciding if it should be approved or not.

relationshipDefs.name: AtlasGlossaryRelatedTerm
relationshipDefs.description: RelatedTerm is a relationship used to say that the linked glossary term may also be of interest. It is like a 'see also' link in a dictionary.

attributeDefs.name: description
attributeDefs.description: The description field can be used to explain why the linked term is of interest.

attributeDefs.name: steward
attributeDefs.description: The steward is the person responsible for assessing the relationship and deciding if it should be approved or not

relationshipDefs.name: AtlasGlossaryIsARelationship
relationshipDefs.description: IsA is a relationship that defines that the 'isA' term is a more generic term than the 'isOf' term. For example, this relationship would be use to say that 'Cat' ISA 'Animal'.

attributeDefs.name: description
attributeDefs.description: The description field can be used to add details about the relationship.

attributeDefs.name: steward
attributeDefs.description: The steward is the person responsible for assessing the relationship and deciding if it should be approved or not.

relationshipDefs.name: AtlasGlossaryTermCategorization
relationshipDefs.description: TermCategorization is a relationship used to organize terms into categories. A term may be linked with many categories and a category may have many terms linked to it. This relationship may connect terms and categories both in the same glossary or in different glossaries.
